  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Education in Emergency for Conflict-affected Girls and Boys in Bornoand        Yobe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overall objective is to increase access to life-saving quality education in emergencies for 25,200 conflict affected-displaced and host community girls and boys of school age children ( 50% girls) in Borno (Ngal and , Bamai) and  Yobe (Gulani) through the (1) establishment of temporary learning spaces (2) establishing gender-sensitive latrines with water and hand washing facilities, (3) provision of essential education in emergency teaching and learning supplies, (4) training of teachers and volunteers on psychosocial support and child-centered pedagogy in emergencies, and (5) enhancing response capacity of SMBCs. The key activities include 

Access: 
	Establishing 26 learning spaces. 
	Rehabilitating 11 existing learning spaces.
	Establishing 20 gender-sensitive WASH facilities at learning spaces.
	Rehabilitant 10 existing WASH facilities.

Quality 
	Training of 264 (50% female) Teachers on PSS and Pedagogy in emergencies.
	Provision of 15,750 school bags. 
	Provision of 280 Recreation kit-in-a-carton. 
	Provision of 180 School-in-a-carton (1 for 40 students).
	Provision of 50 blackboards and chalk. 

Response capacity of Education Service Providers (SBMC)
	Training of 240 (50% female) SBMC members in the role of community in providing education services to out of school children, education in crisis, and education for vulnerable children including girls.
 

These activities will be conducted by UNICEF in partnership with government (State Universal Education Boards/SUBEBs) and non-governmental organization (INTERSOS international)  in Borno (Ngala and Bama) and  Yobe (Gulani) .</narrative>
  </description>
